    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-08T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-08T02:00:00-05:00" n="557"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1593: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-08T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 8, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 8—7:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>784. Following from American Consul General at Nanking, July 7, 4 p.m.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Memorandum from the Chinese Foreign Office dated July 6 reads in translation
                        as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>‘The Ministry of Foreign Affairs has the honor to state that
                                communist bandits are very active in the province of Honan and that
                                efforts are being made to surround and exterminate the bandits.
                                During the period of bandit suppression, it is requested that you
                                instruct American citizens residing in the regions east and west of
                                the railway extending from Chengchow south to the Hupeh border to
                                evacuate temporarily in order to avoid danger’”.</p>
                        </quote>
                    </p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
